title: For Sale:  AR-15, Bushmaster ORC
postcontent:
I’m deciding to part with my AR-15, specifically, it is a Bushmaster XM-15 ORC (Optics Ready Carbine).

The only reason that I’m selling it, is because I need funds to get a carry pistol and pay some bills.  I bought this gun in December of 2012 just before the gun panic started, and I’m of the opinion that the ARs Bushmaster was selling before the panic had slightly better finishes than the ones that were produced during and afterwards. I estimate that there have only been 600 or so rounds put through the rifle, and in that time (no exaggeration) I have not had even one jam or malfunction.  The upgraded parts on the rifle include:

1. aluminum Magpul trigger guard.  (That was a pain to drive the roll pins into, and the only bit of cosmetic damage on the firearm is a scratch near the trigger guard for that reason.)
2. Diamondhead VRS rail system
3. Magpul AFG 2
4. Magpul Miad Grip
5. BMC Gunfighter charging handle 
6. Magpul MS3 sling
7. Magpul MBUS front and rear sights

I will also include the Bushmaster brand 30 round aluminum magazine.

Brand new, the XM-15 ORC costs ~750 (plus NICS background check fee), and I’m selling mine with the few hundred dollars worth of parts for 850.  If you want to purchase it, I will need you to provide a valid OR drivers license or CHL, affirmation that you may legally own the rifle, and fill out a bill of sale.  Cash only and I am not interested in trades, no lowballs please.  

If interested or have questions please text me at REDACTED and ask for A.J.

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Double Barrel PinFire 16g Shotgun (Lafaucheux Civil War)
postcontent:
LaFauncheux-Double Barrel Pin Fire 16g Shotgun Description: 

Civil War era European Pinfire 16 guage double barrel shotgun, Breechloading Pinfire Double Barrel Shotgun made by French manufacturer and inventor LaFauncheux. Stock is cracked in front foregrip although still very firm. Overall still mechanically sound. Aquired from a family member of a former WW1 Veteran who later became a U.S. Secret Police Intelligence Officer for the U.S. Army who spent time over in France durring World War One. Other than the stock being cracked at the front foregrip it is in pretty good condition. Please ask any questions before bidding. More pictures available upon request. 

Very Rare PinFire Shotgun is listed in "Civil War Guns" by William B. Edwards. The Double Barrels are approximately 30 inches long. Bore is good and should clean up without any problem; overall length of this rare PinFire is approximately 46 inches. This nice gun has lower and upper sling swivels all original, as well as everything else. It has an "Under Lever" that pushes to one side for the gun to break-open for loading. As well, it has another "Under Lever" when pushed to the side, allows the barrels to be removed from the Stock and Hammer Section. 

((( Lefaucheux developed a copper based shotshell cartridge in 1836 of rolled paper. ))) Inside the base was a common percussion cap at right angles to the line of bore, and entering the cap thru paper and the base was a copper pin which protruded from the side of the shell about a quarter inch. 

((( Lefaucheux devised the break-open shotgun or rifle ))) with a lever extending forward under the forearm beneath the barrels pushed to one side, disengaging the barrel group and permitting it to move down exposing the breech. The side hammers had flat ends that slammed the cartridge pins in, detonating the cap and the charge. The hammers have to be set on half cock before the barrels will open; the fired shells are then extracted by one's fingers. 

Schuyler, Hartley and Graham sold these guns, and were the major supplier to Civil War Troops. Most of these were used in the South, in and around the Louisiana area. Numerous Lefaucheux shotguns were actually made by Lefaucheux in Paris. Operates as it should in half and full cock, both triggers will bring the hammer down with sufficient force. This is a rare one and will enhance any Civil War, or, any collection. 

Lefaucheux with his manufacturing address engraved on the top middle of the barrell was the original inventor of the Pinfire firearms which later developed in todays rim fire ammunition. This was an original made by his shop before many were made by other manufacturers. 

Thanks! 

Thanks! REDACTED
